 S(s,r)= \sum_{m+n=s}\sum_{i+j=r} \binom{m}{i} \binom{n}{j}, 
 S(s,r) = \sum_{m+n=s} \binom{s}{r} = (s+1) \binom{s}{r} = \frac{(s+1)!}{r!(s-r)!}. 
 S(s,r) = \sum_{i+j=r} \binom{s+1}{r+1} = (r+1) \binom{s+1}{r+1} = \frac{(s+1)!}{r!(s-r)!}. 
